<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920206-0157</DOCNO><DOCID>920206-0157.</DOCID><HL>   Letters to the Editor:   Just Checking</HL><DATE>02/06/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A15</SO><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   As a former naval aviator, when an aircraft is repaired a&quot;post-maintenance check flight&quot; is required. It is performedby a designated &quot;post-maintenance check pilot,&quot; not a &quot;testpilot.&quot; Sen. Tom Harkin was the former, not the latter, asstated in your Dec. 26 Politics andamp; Policy article.   Peter K. Wilke</LP><TEXT>   Laguna Niguel, Calif.</TEXT></DOC>